cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving user experience in navigation systems through the use of augmented reality. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as computer vision techniques are often used in augmented reality systems. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as augmented reality involves overlaying virtual objects onto the real world, which requires graphics rendering. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possibility as some navigation systems may involve robots or autonomous vehicles. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also possible as augmented reality navigation systems often involve multimedia elements such as audio and visual cues.
